	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />How about getting rid of terms like pills and capsules? Most of the game concept is a generic tic-tac-toe or collect-4-in-a-row variarion, somewhat mixed with action elements from tetris. I don't know why Nintendo came up with the pharma scenario, but with the nuts and trees, your game doesn't really match up with that theme anymore.<br />Maybe you can get along without a story, or think of a different story, something like squirrels gathering food for winter, perhaps with some plausible reason for needing to feed/fill/clear/erase the preset items (the ones that are viruses in drmario).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


